The reusable pattern is to keep the underlying tree untyped and lossless, then layer typed wrappers over it. In pseudocode:

```text
enum SyntaxKind { Function, Name, ParameterList, Parameter, Block, Whitespace, Comment, Error }

record SyntaxNode { kind: SyntaxKind, text_range: Range, children: [SyntaxElement] }

record FunctionNode { syntax: SyntaxNode }
FunctionNode.name() -> Option<NameNode>
FunctionNode.parameters() -> Iterator<ParameterNode>
FunctionNode.body() -> Option<BlockNode>
```

The parser produces `SyntaxNode` values including whitespace, comments, and error nodes. Semantic passes use `FunctionNode` and friends. This separation lets formatter/refactoring tools preserve source fidelity while type checking and name resolution see a small, meaningful API.
